Sure! Here are some questions related to communicating and influencing, specifically focused on working together, that may be asked in an interview:

Can you give an example of a situation where you effectively communicated with a team to achieve a common goal?
How do you ensure that all team members are actively engaged and involved in group discussions?
Tell us about a time when you had to handle a conflict within a team. How did you approach it, and what was the outcome?
Describe a project where you had to influence others to adopt a new idea or approach. How did you go about it, and what was the result?
How do you adapt your communication style when working with different team members who have diverse backgrounds or perspectives?
Give an example of a time when you had to collaborate with a difficult team member. How did you handle the situation, and what was the outcome?
How do you ensure that everyone on the team feels valued and their opinions are heard during group discussions?
Describe a situation where you had to lead a team through a challenging task or project. How did you motivate and inspire your team members?
How do you handle miscommunication or misunderstandings within a team? Can you provide an example of when this occurred and how you resolved it?
Give an example of a time when you had to negotiate with others to reach a mutually beneficial agreement. How did you approach the negotiation, and what was the outcome?
Remember, it's important to provide specific examples from your past experiences when answering these questions to demonstrate your abilities in communicating and influencing within a team setting.
